Quote: <i>Play the piano</i>. 3. `To run one's fingers over the backs of sheep to find which are the easiest to shear,' B., 1941: New Zealand, hence Australian, orig. and mostly sheep shearers': C. 20. L.G.D. Acland, `Sheep Station Glossary' in <i>The</i> (Christchurch) <i>Press,</i> 1933-4.
